history.content: Checking graduation requirements would require more time than a drop-in appointment would take. If you could schedule an appointment with an advisor in the CS department, then that would ensure that the two of you can sit down and make sure you are all set to graduate.

I'm trying to double-check to make sure that I will actually graduate this semester. I tried using DARS like I used to, but it looks like it's out of date/non-functional. There's a 0% chance of me getting an advising appointment anytime in the next couple weeks through L&S. Can the CS department advising sort me out on this one during a drop-in appointment? I'm pretty sure everything looks good but I'm a little bit paranoid.
history.subject: Checking Graduation Requirements
